<inglise> (a) "long flax fibre" means flax fibres obtained by complete separation of the fibres and the woody parts of the stalk that are at least 50 cm long on average after scutching and are arranged in parallel strands in bundles, sheets or slivers; </inglise>
<eesti> a) "pikk linakiud" on linakiud, mis on saadud kiu ja varre puitunud osade t&auml;ieliku eraldamise tulemusel ja on p&auml;rast ropsimist keskmiselt v&auml;hemalt 50 cm pikk ning on seatud paralleelsete ribadena kimpudesse, kihtidesse v&otilde;i lintidesse; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) "short flax fibre" means flax fibres other than as referred to in (a) that are obtained by at least partial separation of the fibres and the woody parts of the stalk; </inglise>
<eesti> b) "l&uuml;hike linakiud" on muu kui punktis a osutatud kiud, mis on saadud kiu ja varre puitunud osade v&auml;hemalt osalise eraldamise tulemusena; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) "hemp fibre" means hemp fibres obtained by at least partial separation of the fibres and the woody parts of the stalk. </inglise>
<eesti> c) "kanepikiud" on kanepikiud, mis on saadud kiu ja varre puitunud osade v&auml;hemalt osalise eraldamise tulemusena. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Authorisation of primary processors </inglise>
<eesti> Esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate heakskiitmine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Primary processors must submit applications for authorisation to the competent authorities including at least: </inglise>
<eesti> Esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejad peavad esitama p&auml;devatele asutustele loataotluse, milles on esitatud v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) a description of the undertaking and of the full range of products obtained by processing flax and hemp straw; </inglise>
<eesti> a) ettev&otilde;tja ning k&otilde;ikide lina- ja kanepivarte t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel saadud toodete kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) a description of the processing plant and equipment, giving details of their location and technical specifications covering: </inglise>
<eesti> b) t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;tte ja seadmete kirjeldus, mis sisaldab nende asukoha ja tehniliste n&auml;itajate j&auml;rgmisi &uuml;ksikasju: </eesti>
<inglise> - energy consumption and the maximum quantities of flax and hemp straw that can be processed per hour and per year, </inglise>
<eesti> - energiatarbimist ning lina- ja kanepivarte suurimaid koguseid, mida on v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;delda tunnis ja aastas, </eesti>
<inglise> - the maximum quantities of long flax fibre, short flax fibre and hemp fibre that can be obtained per hour and per year, </inglise>
<eesti> - pika linakiu, l&uuml;hikese linakiu ja kanepikiu suurimaid koguseid, mida on v&otilde;imalik saada tunnis ja aastas, </eesti>
<inglise> - the indicative quantities of flax and hemp straw required to obtain 100 kg of each product referred to in (a); </inglise>
<eesti> - lina- ja kanepivarte soovituslik kogus 100 kg iga punktis a osutatud toote saamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) a description of the storage facilities, giving details of their location and capacity in tonnes of flax and hemp straw and fibre. </inglise>
<eesti> c) ladustamisrajatiste kirjeldus, milles on &uuml;ksikasjad nende asukoha ning lina- ja kanepivarte ja lina- ja kanepikiu mahutavuse kohta tonnides. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member State may waive the requirement on primary processors approved for the 2000/01 marketing year under Article 3 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 619/71(15) to submit information that is already available, provided that the primary processors in question declare that there has been no change in the situation. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 (15) artikli 3 kohaselt 2000/01. turustusaastaks heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejad vabastada juba k&auml;ttesaadavate andmete esitamisest, tingimusel et k&otilde;nealused esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejad kinnitavad, et olukord ei ole muutunud. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Applications for authorisation shall include an undertaking applying from the date of submission to: </inglise>
<eesti> Loataotluse esitamisega v&otilde;tab esitaja j&auml;rgmised taotluse esitamise kuup&auml;evast kehtivad kohustused: </eesti>
<inglise> - store separately by marketing year of harvest of the straw concerned and by Member State of harvest, flax straw, hemp straw, long flax fibre, short flax fibre and hemp fibre: </inglise>
<eesti> - ladustada eraldi saagikoristuse turustusaastate kaupa asjakohased varred ning saagi koristanud liikmesriikide kaupa linavarred, kanepivarred, pikk linakiud, l&uuml;hike linakiud ja kanepikiud, mis on saadud: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) covered by all sale/purchase contracts and processing commitments combined, </inglise>
<eesti> a) vastavalt k&otilde;ikidele ostu-m&uuml;&uuml;gilepingutele ja t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiskohustustele, </eesti>
<inglise> (b) covered by each processing contract concluded with persons treated as processors, </inglise>
<eesti> b) vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;tlejatena k&auml;sitatavate isikutega s&otilde;lmitud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemislepingutele, </eesti>
<inglise> (c) from all other suppliers combined and, where applicable, corresponding to batches of fibre obtained from straw falling within (a) but not to be covered by an aid application, </inglise>
<eesti> c) k&otilde;igilt &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud tarnijatelt ning vajaduse korral kiu partiidest, mis on saadud punktile a vastavatest vartest, mille kohta toetust ei taotleta, </eesti>
<inglise> - keep daily records of stocks, linked regularly to financial accounts, and of the information specified in paragraph 4, together with supporting documents as specified by the Member State for the purpose of controls, </inglise>
<eesti> - pidada kontrolli eesm&auml;rgil igap&auml;evast laoarvestust, mis lisatakse regulaarselt raamatupidamisele, ja koguda l&otilde;ikes 4 m&auml;&auml;ratletud teavet koos liikmesriikide t&auml;psustatud t&auml;iendavate dokumentidega, </eesti>
<inglise> - notify the competent authority of any changes in the information covered by paragraph 1, </inglise>
<eesti> - teavitada p&auml;devaid asutusi k&otilde;igist muutustest l&otilde;ikega 1 h&otilde;lmatud teabes, </eesti>
<inglise> - undergo any checks required under the aid scheme provided for in Regulation (EC) No 1673/2000. </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;imaldada k&otilde;igi m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1673/2000 s&auml;testatud toetuskava raames n&otilde;utavate kontrollide l&auml;biviimist. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> After an on-the-spot inspection to check that the information covered by paragraph 1 tallies with the facts, the competent authority shall grant primary processors authorisation covering the types of fibre meeting the conditions for eligibility for the aid which they may produce and shall allocate an authorisation number to each. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kohapealse kontrolliga on tuvastatud, et l&otilde;ikega 1 h&otilde;lmatud teave on faktidega vastavuses, annavad p&auml;devad asutused esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejale loa toetuse saamise tingimustele vastavate kiut&uuml;&uuml;pide osas, mida nad v&otilde;ivad toota, ning loa numbri. </eesti>
<inglise> Authorisation shall be granted within two months of submission of applications. </inglise>
<eesti> Luba antakse kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast taotluse esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Where there is a change in one or more items of information covered by paragraph 1, the competent authority shall confirm or adjust authorisations, where necessary after an on-the-spot check, in the month following that of notification of the change. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui l&otilde;ikega 1 h&otilde;lmatud teabes on &uuml;ks muudatus v&otilde;i rohkem, kinnitavad p&auml;devad asutused loa v&otilde;i kohandavad seda vajaduse korral, vajadusel p&auml;rast kohapealset kontrolli, kuu aja jooksul alates muudatusest teatamisest. </eesti>
<inglise> However, any adjustment affecting the types of fibre covered by authorisations granted may take effect only from the following marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> Loaga h&otilde;lmatud kiut&uuml;&uuml;pe m&otilde;jutavad kohandused j&otilde;ustuvad siiski alles j&auml;rgmisest turustusaastast alates. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> In connection with the authorisation of primary processors in respect of long flax fibre and simultaneously in respect of short flax fibre, the Member States may allow short flax fibre to be cleaned under the conditions laid down in this paragraph and if it considers the control arrangements to be satisfactory, so that the fibre complies with the impurity and shive limits laid down in Article 2(3) (b) of Regulation (EC) No 1673/2000. </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate heakskiitmisega pika linakiu ja &uuml;htlasi ka l&uuml;hikese linakiu osas v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid lubada l&uuml;hikese linakiu puhastamist k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tingimuste kohaselt, kui nad leiavad, et kontrollimeetmed on rahuldavad, nii et kiud vastab m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1673/2000 artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 3 punktis b s&auml;testatud lisandite ja linaluude sisalduse piirnormidele. </eesti>
<inglise> In such cases primary processors shall state their intention to make use of the provisions of this paragraph in their applications for authorisation as provided for in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellisel juhul teatavad esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejad oma loataotlustes kavatsusest kasutada k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike s&auml;tteid l&otilde;ikes 1 etten&auml;htud viisil. </eesti>
<inglise> Only one cleaner of short flax fibre may be granted authorisation per authorised primary processor per marketing year concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaomasel turustusaastal antakse luba ainult &uuml;hele l&uuml;hikest linakiudu puhastavale ettev&otilde;ttele iga heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tleja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Before 1 February in respect of each marketing year, authorised primary processors shall present the competent authorities with a contract for the cleaning of short flax fibre, including at least: </inglise>
<eesti> Igal turustusaastal esitavad heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejad p&auml;devatele asutustele enne 1. veebruari l&uuml;hikese linakiu puhastamise lepingu, mis sisaldab v&auml;hemalt: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the date of conclusion of the contract and the marketing year corresponding to the harvest of the straw from which the fibre concerned has been obtained; </inglise>
<eesti> a) lepingu s&otilde;lmimise kuup&auml;eva ja turustusaastat, mis vastab linavarte saagikoristusele, millest asjaomane kiud on saadud; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the primary processor's authorisation number and, in the case of cleaners of short flax fibre, their names, business names and addresses and the location of the plant; </inglise>
<eesti> b) esmat&ouml;&ouml;tleja loanumbrit ning l&uuml;hikese linakiu puhastaja nime, ettev&otilde;tte nime, aadressi ja asukohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) a statement to the effect that the cleaner of short flax fibre undertakes to: </inglise>
<eesti> c) avaldust, et l&uuml;hikese linakiu puhastaja kohustub: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) store cleaned and uncleaned short flax fibre separately by cleaning contract, </inglise>
<eesti> i) vastavalt puhastamislepingule ladustama eraldi puhastatud ja puhastamata l&uuml;hikest linakiudu, </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) keep separately by cleaning contract, daily records of the quantities of uncleaned short flax fibre entering the undertaking, the quantities of cleaned short flax fibre obtained, and the quantities of each in storage, </inglise>
<eesti> ii) vastavalt puhastamislepingule pidama iga p&auml;ev eraldi arvestust ettev&otilde;ttesse toodud puhastamata l&uuml;hikese linakiu ja sellest saadud puhastatud l&uuml;hikese linakiu koguste kohta ning nende koguste kohta laos, </eesti>
<inglise> (iii) keep supporting documents as specified by the Member State for the purposes of controls and undergo any checks required under this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> iii) s&auml;ilitama kontrollimiseks liikmesriigi poolt etten&auml;htud t&auml;iendavaid dokumente ning v&otilde;imaldama l&auml;bi viia k&otilde;iki k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud kontrolle. </eesti>
<inglise> Cleaners' undertakings as referred to in point (c) shall be deemed to be undertakings of primary processors under their authorisations. </inglise>
<eesti> Puhastajate punktis c osutatud kohustusi k&auml;sitakse esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate loa alusel s&otilde;lmitud kohustustena. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Stock records of authorised primary processors shall specify, by day and by category of straw or type of fibre stored separately: </inglise>
<eesti> Heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate laoarvestuses t&auml;psustatakse p&auml;evade ning eraldi ladustatud varte kategooria v&otilde;i kiu liikide kaupa: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the quantities entering the undertaking and covered by each contract or commitment as referred to in Article 5 and, where applicable, from each other supplier; </inglise>
<eesti> a) iga artiklis 5 osutatud lepingu v&otilde;i kohustusega h&otilde;lmatud ja vajaduse korral ka teiste tarnijate poolt ettev&otilde;ttesse toodud kogused; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the quantities of straw processed and the quantities of fibre obtained; </inglise>
<eesti> b) t&ouml;&ouml;deldud varte ja neist saadud kiu kogused; </eesti>
