<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> Controls </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollid </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Controls shall be performed to ensure compliance with the conditions for granting the aid and shall in particular involve: </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrolle viiakse l&auml;bi, et kindlustada toetuse saamise tingimuste t&auml;itmist ja eelk&otilde;ige et: </eesti>
<inglise> - checking compliance with the conditions for authorising primary processors and fulfilment of their obligations by persons treated as processors, </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollida esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate vastavust heakskiitmise tingimustele ning t&ouml;&ouml;tlejatena k&auml;sitatavate isikute kohustuste t&auml;itmist, </eesti>
<inglise> - comparing information on agricultural parcels referred to in sale/purchase contracts, processing commitments and processing contracts to see whether it tallies with that determined in accordance with Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999, </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;rrelda ostu-m&uuml;&uuml;gilepingutes, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiskohustustes ja t&ouml;&ouml;tlemislepingutes osutatud teavet p&otilde;llumajanduslike maat&uuml;kkide kohta, et n&auml;ha, kas see on koosk&otilde;las vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratuga, </eesti>
<inglise> - checking information in support of quantities covered by aid applications from authorised primary processors and persons treated as processors. </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollida teavet koguste kohta, mille puhul heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejad ja t&ouml;&ouml;tlejatena k&auml;sitatavad isikud toetust taotlevad. </eesti>
<inglise> Checks of authorised primary processors carried out by the competent authorities of Member States shall cover the processing of all flax and hemp straw grown for fibre produced in the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide p&auml;devate asutuste tehtavad heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate kontrollid h&otilde;lmavad kogu kiu tootmiseks &uuml;henduses kasvatatava lina ja kanepi varte t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> On-the-spot inspections conducted for the purposes of controls as provided for in paragraph 1 shall be decided by the competent authorities, in particular on the basis of a risk analysis, with a view to checking at least 75 % of authorised primary processors and 10 % of persons treated as processors per marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;devad asutused m&auml;&auml;ravad l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kontrollimisteks kohapealsed kontrollid eelk&otilde;ige riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si p&otilde;hjal, et kontrollida turustusaasta jooksul v&auml;hemalt 75% heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejatest ja 10% t&ouml;&ouml;tlejatena k&auml;sitatavatest isikutest. </eesti>
<inglise> However, in no case may the number of on-the-spot inspections conducted in any Member State be less than the total number of hectares declared as under flax and hemp in that Member State, divided by 750. </inglise>
<eesti> Siiski ei v&otilde;i &uuml;heski liikmesriigis tehtud kohapealsete kontrollide arv olla mingil juhul v&auml;iksem kui asjaomases liikmesriigis lina ja kanepi kasvatamiseks deklareeritud hektarite koguarv, mis on jagatud 750ga. </eesti>
<inglise> On-the-spot inspections shall also cover all cleaners of short flax fibre who have concluded contracts with authorised primary processors for the cleaning of fibre. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohapealsed kontrollid h&otilde;lmavad ka k&otilde;iki l&uuml;hikese linakiu puhastajaid, kes on heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejatega s&otilde;lminud lepingud kiu puhastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> On-the-spot inspections shall in particular involve checking: </inglise>
<eesti> Kohapealsete kontrollide k&auml;igus kontrollitakse eelk&otilde;ige: </eesti>
<inglise> - plant, stocks and fibre obtained, </inglise>
<eesti> - tootmisettev&otilde;tet, ladusid ja saadud kiudu, </eesti>
<inglise> - stock records and financial accounts, </inglise>
<eesti> - laoarvestust ja raamatupidamist, </eesti>
<inglise> - the energy consumed by the various means of production and documents relating to labour employed, and </inglise>
<eesti> - dokumente mitmesuguste tootmisvahendite energiatarbimise ja t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u kohta ja </eesti>
<inglise> - any commercial documents relevant to controls. </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;iki kontrollimise seisukohalt asjakohaseid &auml;ridokumente. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of doubt as to the eligibility of fibre, and in particular as regards the impurities content of short flax fibre or hemp fibre, a representative sample shall be taken from the batches called into question and a precise determination carried out of the relevant characteristics. </inglise>
<eesti> Kahtluse korral, kas kiud vastab toetuse saamise tingimustele, eriti lisandite sisalduse osas l&uuml;hikeses linakius ja kanepikius, v&otilde;etakse kahtlusalustest partiidest proov ja m&auml;&auml;ratakse asjakohased omadused t&auml;pselt kindlaks. </eesti>
<inglise> Where applicable and depending on the circumstances, the Member State shall determine the quantities that are not eligible among those covered by aid applications. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajaduse korral ja s&otilde;ltuvalt asjaoludest m&auml;&auml;rab liikmesriik toetuse taotlusega h&otilde;lmatud koguste hulgast kindlaks need kogused, mis toetuse saamise tingimustele ei vasta. </eesti>
<inglise> In cases as referred to in Article 3(3) of Regulation (EC) No 1673/2000, the Member State conducting the inspection shall send the findings immediately to the Member State that is to pay the aid. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1673/2000 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud juhtudel teatab kontrollinud liikmesriik avastatud puudustest viivitamata liikmesriigile, kes toetust maksab. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> Penalties </inglise>
<eesti> Karistused </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where checks show that undertakings entered into in authorisation applications are not fulfilled, authorisation shall be withdrawn immediately and, notwithstanding Article 3(3), primary processors whose authorisation has been withdrawn shall not be granted any further authorisation before the second marketing year beginning after the date of the check or the date on which any failure to fulfil such undertakings has been established. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kontrollimine n&auml;itab, et loa taotlusega v&otilde;etud kohustusi ei ole t&auml;idetud, t&uuml;histatakse luba viivitamata ning olenemata artikli 3 l&otilde;ikest 3, ei anta t&uuml;histatud loaga esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejatele uut luba enne kontrollimise p&auml;evale v&otilde;i kohustuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise tuvastamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneva teise turustusaasta algust. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a false declaration is made deliberately or as a result of serious negligence or where the primary processor has signed sale/purchase contracts covering straw or has entered into processing commitments covering a number of hectares which would normally provide a significantly higher output than can be processed in accordance with the technical specifications shown in his authorisation, the authorised primary processor or person treated as a processor shall not qualify for processing aid or, where applicable, for additional aid as provided for in Article 4 of Regulation (EC) No 1673/2000 in respect of the marketing year concerned and the following marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui valeandmed on esitatud tahtlikult v&otilde;i t&otilde;sise hooletuse t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i kui esmat&ouml;&ouml;tleja on allkirjastanud varte ostu-m&uuml;&uuml;gilepingu v&otilde;i s&otilde;lminud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiskohustuse hektarite arvu kohta, mis tavaliselt n&auml;eks ette oluliselt k&otilde;rgema toodangu, kui on v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;delda vastavalt loataotluses esitatud tehnilisele n&auml;itajatele, ei ole heakskiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejal v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlejana k&auml;sitataval isikul &otilde;igust saada t&ouml;&ouml;tlemistoetust v&otilde;i vajaduse korral m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1673/2000 artiklis 4 s&auml;testatud t&auml;iendavat toetust asjakohasel turustusaastal ning j&auml;rgneval turustusaastal. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where quantities of long flax fibre, short flax fibre or hemp fibre covered by aid applications are found to exceed those meeting the conditions for eligibility for the aid and actually obtained in respect of a period as referred to in Article 6(2), the aid that may be granted on each type of fibre shall, without prejudice to Article 8(3), be calculated on the basis of the quantities actually eligible in respect of the marketing year concerned, less twice the difference with those covered by aid applications. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tehakse kindlaks, et pika linakiu, l&uuml;hikese linakiu v&otilde;i kanepikiu kogused, mille kohta toetust on taotletud, on suuremad kui artikli 6 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud ajaperioodi jooksul tegelikult saadud toetuse saamise tingimustele vastava kiu koguseid, arvutatakse toetus, mida v&otilde;idakse iga kiuliigi puhul anda, toetuse saamise tingimustele vastavate asjaomase turustusaasta tegelike koguste alusel, millest on lahutatud kahekordne taotletud koguseid &uuml;letav m&auml;&auml;r, ilma et see piiraks artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Except in cases of force majeure, in the event of late submission of aid applications as provided for in Article 9 or of late submission or late declaration of information as provided for in Article 6, the aid applied for and which the party concerned would have been entitled to if the application had been submitted or declared by the deadline shall be reduced by 1 % per working day. </inglise>
<eesti> V&auml;lja arvatud v&auml;&auml;ramatu j&otilde;u puhul, v&auml;hendatakse artiklis 9 s&auml;testatud toetuse taotluste esitamise hilinemisel v&otilde;i artiklis 6 s&auml;testatud teabe esitamise v&otilde;i deklareerimise hilinemisel taotletud toetust, mida asjaomasel isikul oleks olnud &otilde;igus saada, kui ta oleks &otilde;igeks ajaks esitanud taotluse v&otilde;i teabe, 1% iga t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Applications and information as provided for in Article 6(1) submitted more than 25 days late shall be inadmissible. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui hilinetakse rohkem kui 25 p&auml;eva, siis artikli 6 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud taotlusi ja teavet vastu ei v&otilde;eta. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Where applicable, the additional aid referred to in Article 11 shall be reduced by the same percentage as that applied to the total processing aid granted in respect of the marketing year concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajaduse korral v&auml;hendatakse artiklis 11 osutatud t&auml;iendavat toetust sama protsendim&auml;&auml;ra v&otilde;rra kui kogu asjaomasel turustusaastal antud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemistoetust. </eesti>
